{
  "texts": [
    "With regard specifically to operations, DL operations are typically simpler to undertake than ML operations.",
    "DL brought models of simpler application and design than traditional ML models (Shao et al. 2022).",
    "Feature extraction and classifier learning are done concurrently in an end-to-end way.",
    "DL also facilitates data engineering, as building blocks or layers are directly transposable between different analysis or tasks.",
    "This former point led to the emergence of toolkits that helped to widely disseminate the methods."
  ]
}